.TH "drm_plane_from_index" 9 "drm_plane_from_index" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
drm_plane_from_index \- find the registered plane at an index
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "struct drm_plane *" drm_plane_from_index
.BI "(struct drm_device *dev "  ","
.BI "int idx "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dev" 12
DRM device
.IP "idx" 12
index of registered plane to find for
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Given a plane index, return the registered plane from DRM device's
list of planes with matching index. This is the inverse of \fBdrm_plane_index\fP.
